Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[It seems there may be an outbreak of some sort and perhaps clinical signs are not as clear cut as the agency would like, and perhaps they are awaiting laboratory confirmation if they are dealing with a single disease or multiple diseases. Both of these diseases are contagious. While strangles is serious, it is more easily treated. Equine herpesvirus is a disease that is difficult to treat and can have devastating consequences. We look forward to a definitive diagnosis on these horses. - Mod.TG

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4860983,230.]
